-- McKesson Shares Drop After Baird Says Top Client Alleges Contract Breach
-- B y   L u   W a n g
-- 2010-09-23T15:56:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/mckesson-shares-drop-after-baird-says-top-client-alleges-contract-breach.html
McKesson Corp. dropped after Robert
W. Baird & Co. said Independent Pharmacy Cooperative, one of the
drug distributor’s top five customers, filed a lawsuit alleging
the company of a breach of contract.   The stock had the second-biggest decline in the Standard &
Poor’s 500 Index, sliding 3.8 percent to $59.80 as of 11:55 a.m.
in New York. Ana Schrank, a spokesperson for McKesson, didn’t
immediately return a telephone call seeking comment.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Lu Wang in New York at 
